column52:
410968: GILP (Python Package)
In both the simplex and branch  bound lab, we use a python package called gilp. This python package generated the linear programming visualizations in these labs (recall the isoprofit slider and rotating 3d LP feasible regions). The remaining questions ask about the python package itself as well as the labs that used it.
